# Google AI Studio → https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# Server-only — never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ (that would leak the key to every browser).
#
# Every person who uses your deployed site shares this one key: their browser calls YOUR
# /api/video/* and /api/gemini routes; Next.js reads this env on the server and calls Google.
# Add GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY (and optional vars below) in your host’s dashboard
# (e.g. Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables) for Production / Preview —
# not only in .env.local on your laptop.
#
# If generations fail in production: confirm the key is set for that environment. If you use
# Google Cloud “Application restrictions”, HTTP referrer rules are for browser keys; server-side
# Node requests may be blocked — prefer an unrestricted AI Studio key or appropriate API
# restrictions for server use.
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=
# Imagen (AI Photo in Create) — Imagen 3 is retired; defaults try imagen-4.0-fast / generate / ultra.
# IMAGEN_MODEL=imagen-4.0-generate-001
# Optional override (default: gemini-2.0-flash)
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-1.5-flash
# If the primary model hits rate limits (HTTP 429), the app retries with backoff, then tries this
# model, then gemini-1.5-flash.
# GEMINI_MODEL_FALLBACK=gemini-1.5-flash-8b
# Veo (AI video) — see https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/video and pricing:
# https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing#veo-3.1
#
# Default in code is the Fast preview model (lower $/s than Standard full-quality).
# VEO_MODEL=veo-3.1-fast-generate-preview
#
# Optional cost / size knobs (defaults in code: OPTIMIZED compression, 720p, 5s when unset):
# VEO_GENERATE_AUDIO=false          # Smaller files; silent clips unless you enable audio.
# VEO_VIDEO_DURATION_SECONDS=5     # Shorter = smaller files & lower API cost (1–60).
# VEO_VIDEO_RESOLUTION=720p        # 1080p/4k = much larger Blob usage.
# VEO_VIDEO_RESOLUTION=480p        # Not native — app uses 720p + OPTIMIZED (smallest practical).
# VEO_VIDEO_COMPRESSION=optimized   # Implicit default. Use "lossless" only if you need max quality.

# Nomi media — Vercel Blob (public URLs for videos/images in feeds). Create in Vercel → Storage → Blob.
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# Nomi accounts & posts — Upstash Redis (production / shared persistence).
# Option A — REST (recommended): both from Upstash dashboard → REST API.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://YOUR-DB.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
#
# Option B — one line (paste the redis://… string from Upstash “Redis CLI” / connect dialog):
# UPSTASH_REDIS_URL=redis://default:YOUR_TOKEN@YOUR-DB.upstash.io:6379
#
# Required on Vercel: without Redis, each server is “amnesiac” — new accounts vanish after refresh and
# login will fail. There is no shared file on serverless.
#
# Emergency only (do not use in production): allow auth into ephemeral memory on Vercel.
# NOMI_ALLOW_EPHEMERAL_AUTH=1
#
# Without Redis: local JSON at data/nomi-cloud.json whenever this app is NOT on Vercel (next dev,
# next start, self-hosted). On Vercel you must use Redis — there is no shared disk.
#
# One-time: copy your local dev DB (data/nomi-cloud.json, gitignored) into Redis for production:
#   npm run db:import-redis
# Large JSON can take a minute. If Redis already has bad data: npm run db:import-redis -- --replace-remote
# (Set Redis env in .env.local or the shell; the script reads .env.local automatically.)
# Check deploy: GET …/api/nomi/health → redis:true, blob:true
#
# Local verification: npm run dev (or start) then npm run test:smoke
# Full one-shot: npm run test:ci  (build + production server + API smoke on port 3999)
